bush lawyer
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:<i>Rubus cissoides</i>, a tenacious vine of the spp. Rosaceae notorious for trapping and starving sheep.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: a tenacious indigenous bramble, ,<i>Rubus australis</i>, taramoa,  or tataramoa, with small white flowers, renowned for forming barriers on bush paths. It was also well-known by the jocular sobriquet of taihoa, wait-a-while, or wait-a-bit.
